    "(ii), a temporally causal CNN processes the intermediate sequence u 0:L-1 (Ξ), across space and time into tokens Z 0:L-1.",
    "Mapping irregular inputs onto a regular grid-aligned space, allows ENMA to leverage convolutional inductive biases of the CNN for efficient and coherent compression.",
    "Decoding mirrors the encoder structure.",
    "The encoder and decoder are optimized jointly with a VAE loss: L = L recon + β • L KL.",
    "To improve robustness to varying input sparsity, we randomly subsample the spatial grid at training time: the number of input points varies between 20% and 100% of the full grid X."
